        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 22 at 10:06PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1006 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Floris, or 10 miles northwest of Beaver, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forgan, Mocane, and Floris.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Oklahoma.</instruction>
